Hey, I’m stuck for a long time with this. I’m using rxandroid. I have an Observable on location and another on a retrofit task, the thing is how can I make the observer what for location then call the retrofit observer… In order to perform the retrofit task I need the latitude and longitude provided by the locationService
what I get so far

mlocationService.getLocation()
				.timeout(LOCATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
				.subscribeOn(Schedulers.newThread())
				.observeOn(AndroidSchedulers.mainThread())
				.subscribe(location -&gt; {
					mMapView.getMapAsync(mapboxMap -&gt; {
						CameraPosition position = new CameraPosition.Builder()
								.target(new LatLng(location.getLatitude(), location.getLongitude()))
								.zoom(15)
								.build();
						mapboxMap.animateCamera(CameraUpdateFactory.newCameraPosition(position), 5000);
					});
				});

Now my problem is to subscribe to the retrofit observable parsing the data that come from location
kinda synchronous thing
